==English==

===Etymology===
From Latin ''[[renegare]]'', from ''[[negare]]'' ("to [[deny]]"). See also ''[[renegade]]''.

===Pronunciation===
*IPA: /rɪˈnɛg/ (''Am. E.''), /rɪˈneg/ (''Am. E.''), /rɪˈni:g/ (''Br. E.'')
*{{audio|en-us-renege.ogg|Audio (US)}}, {{audio|en-us-renege2.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Verb===
{{en-verb|reneg|ing}}

#{{intransitive}} To [[break]] a [[promise]] or [[commitment]]; to go back on one's [[word]].
#{{intransitive}} In a [[card game]], to break one's commitment to [[follow suit]] when capable.
#{{transitive}} {{archaic}} To [[deny]]; to [[renounce]]

